item.description:
Dashing through the field, with glow-sticks we do play,
Catching discs up high, laughing all the way. (ha ha ha!)
We start at seven please, I will bring the light,
What fun will be is toss some discs tonight.

Chorus
OOOOH,
Frisbee bells, frisbee bells, frisbee all the way!
O what fun it is to catch and throw all day. HEY!
Frisbee bells, frisbee bells, frisbee all the way!
O what fun it is to catch and throw all day. HEY!

A day or two ahead, frisbee will be so fun,
Cambridge Common is where, you will surely run!
It's tuesday night like 'fore, no we will not freeze;
All are glad to come, especially the newbies!

(Chorus)

Now that it is cold, you cannot snooze,
but do come with glee-- how can you refuse?
We will play all night, or until nine or ten,
And after the game, the fun does not end!

(Chorus)

After we do turn blue, we will not disband,
but rather go to warmth; trust it will not be bland!
So do come on by, and don't eat an orange,
because I will fail to rhyme, something something shmorange!

(Chorus)
item.name: Frisbee Bells on Cambridge Common
